(29, 1, 'sess_20250601_183209_c1b342b23932bebe', 'conv_sess_20250601_183209_c1b342b23932bebe_1748802775', NULL, 'user', 'how do i list files?', '2025-06-01 18:32:55', '[]', NULL, NULL, 'local', NULL, 0, NULL, 0),
(30, 1, 'sess_20250601_183209_c1b342b23932bebe', 'conv_sess_20250601_183209_c1b342b23932bebe_1748802775', NULL, 'bot', 'To list files and directories in Windows, you can use several commands:\n\n• **dir** - Basic directory listing\n• **dir /a** - Show all files including hidden\n• **dir /s** - Include subdirectories\n• **tree** - Show directory structure as a tree\n\nThe most common is simply **dir** to see what\'s in the current directory.', '2025-06-01 18:32:55', '{\"knowledge_id\":1}', 0.066, NULL, 'local', 'dir', 0, NULL, 0),
